 tomatoes"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"50 g tomato paste"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 - 2 tsp white sugar, to taste"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 tsp ground cumin"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 tsp ground coriander"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 tsp dried oregano"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 tsp smoked paprika"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 tsp Vegetable stock paste (see Tips)"},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Spicy eggs"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"oil, for greasing"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"4 whole eggs"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"8 pinches dried chilli flakes"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"4 pinches salt"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"4 pinches ground black pepper"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"2 sprigs fresh coriander, leaves only"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"500 g boiling water"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"labne, to serve (optional - see Tips)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"flatbreads, to serve"}],"nutrition":["per 1 portion","1186.1 kJ \/ 282.4 kcal","10.9 g","18 g","17.6 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i> for the Vegetable stock paste recipe.","If you do not have egg rings, eggs can be broken directly onto lined Varoma tray. Cooking time may vary.","To make your own labne (a soft yoghurt cheese), please refer to the recipes on www.cookidoo.com.au. You can also replace the labne with Danish feta or soft goat's cheese."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","30m","4 portions"]}